observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the prescribed property ledger cards for Local Road Networks and disclose the complete description information for the said property in the Notes to Financial Statements;
b. General Services Office to prepare and maintain road networks property ledger cards and to prepare and submit Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System (RPCPPE);
c. Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
d. Inventory Committee to conduct inventory count and submit report on the physical count of the Road Network as of year end.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. prioritize and undertake the necessary action to complete the approved 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan as prescribed by R.A 9003;
b. create the position of the Municipal Environmental Officer who will take authority over the functions, duties and responsibilities attached thereto, in coordination with the Municipal Waste Management Board;
c. designate MENRO to oversee implementation of the MSWM activities; and
d. ensure the effective implementation of the MSWM Plan.
(Other specific actions included compliance with DBM and NSWMC requirements.)
